

On webpage create Network that gives a network_id this is our control plane

curl -s https://install.zerotier.com | sudo bash
# repo created
cat /etc/apt/source.list.d/zerotier.list
# service
systemctl status zerotier-one
# key-pair generated
/var/lib/zerotier-one/identity.public
/var/lib/zerotier-one/identity.secret

zerotier-cli info  # get address
zerotier-cli peers  # server will communicate first with root servers to discovery
                    # role: PLANET -> main root servers
                    # role: LEAF   -> that is directly connected
host root.zerotier.com # get info of root servers

zerotier-cli join <network_id>  # join network


zerotier-cli listnetworks # will have ACCESS_DENIED
                          # in controlled must be approve.

if 2 nodes connect, zerotier talks directly to each other; zerotier dynamically builds a peer-to-peer network
The tecnique is called the UDP Hall punching, that is used to connect 2 devices on a network when they are both behind NAT
Root server will coordinate the communication of both by sending them their public address, the firewall will interpret the other party's initialization packet as a reply in a two-way UDP connection, one established, the node talks to each other directly.
If the UDP Hall punching connection cannot be established, the root server will rely packages.
